; xinput1_3.def -- pin the XInput export ORDINALS to match the real XInput1_3.dll.
;
; DOOM imports XINPUT1_3.dll BY ORDINAL (dumpbin /imports DOOMx64vk: "Ordinal 2", "Ordinal 3" = the only
; two it pulls -- XInputGetState + XInputSetState). MSVC's default __declspec(dllexport) numbers exports
; ALPHABETICALLY, which put XInputGetBatteryInformation at ordinal 2 and XInputGetCapabilities at 3. So
; DOOM's per-frame controller poll (XInputGetState, ord 2) landed in our XInputGetBatteryInformation, whose
; real-fn forward writes a battery struct through an uninitialised 3rd pointer -> wild heap write ->
; 0xC0000374 heap corruption, but ONLY on a machine with a controller (keyboard/mouse never polls XInput).
;
; This .def fixes the ordinals. The function BODIES stay in xinput_proxy.c (the dllexport there is removed
; so this .def is the SOLE export source -- avoids an LNK4197 double-export). Ordinals are verified against
; C:\Windows\System32\XInput1_3.dll (2=GetState 3=SetState 4=GetCapabilities 5=Enable 6=DSound 7=Battery
; 8=Keystroke). The OG SnapHak XINPUT1_3.dll had the same alphabetical defect (latent; few used a pad).
EXPORTS
    XInputGetState                  @2
    XInputSetState                  @3
    XInputGetCapabilities           @4
    XInputEnable                    @5
    XInputGetDSoundAudioDeviceGuids @6
    XInputGetBatteryInformation     @7
    XInputGetKeystroke              @8
